    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-04T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-04T02:00:00-05:00" n="396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8410: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-04T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 4, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 4—1:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>588. Embassy’s 583, December 3, 3 p.m. Following telegram has been received from
                    Tsingtau: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 4, 10 a.m. Situation remains quiet. Chinese who were arrested
                            have been released. Chinese authorities regard Japanese action as
                            designed to force out present Mayor and his administration.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Nanking informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
